## REST API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Auth Required | Description |
| :-- | :-- | :-- | :-- |
| `GET` | `/api/csrf-token` | None | Fetch CSRF token for the current session |
| `POST` | `/api/login` | None | Authenticate user and establish session |
| `POST` | `/api/register` | None | Register a new user account |
| `POST` | `/api/logout` | User | Destroy the current session |
| `POST` | `/api/change-password` | User | Change authenticated user's own password |
| `GET` | `/api/categories` | None | List all product categories |
| `POST` | `/api/categories` | Admin | Create a new category |
| `PUT` | `/api/categories/:id` | Admin | Update an existing category |
| `DELETE` | `/api/categories/:id` | Admin | Delete a category |
| `GET` | `/api/products` | None | List products, optionally filtered by category |
| `POST` | `/api/products` | Admin | Create a new product with image upload |
| `PUT` | `/api/products/:id` | Admin | Update an existing product |
| `DELETE` | `/api/products/:id` | Admin | Delete a product |


***

## Project File Structure

| Path | Description |
| :-- | :-- |
| `server.js` | Main Express application — routes, middleware, session, CSRF |
| `database.js` | SQLite database initialization and schema setup |
| `package.json` | Node.js dependency manifest |
| `shopping.db` | SQLite database file |
| `nginx-config.txt` | Nginx configuration backup |
| `public/index.html` | Homepage and product listing |
| `public/product.html` | Individual product detail page |
| `public/login.html` | User login page |
| `public/register.html` | User registration page |
| `public/admin.html` | Admin panel (protected) |
| `public/change-password.html` | Password change page |
| `public/js/` | All frontend JavaScript modules |
| `public/css/` | All stylesheets |
| `public/images/` | Product images and thumbnails |


***

## Deployment Process

1. **Upload files** to the server securely via SCP using SSH key-based authentication
2. **Install all Node.js dependencies** from within the `/var/www/html` application directory using npm
3. **Start the application** using PM2 with a named process, then save the process list and register the PM2 startup hook so the app survives VM reboots
4. **Issue a TLS certificate** for the domain using Certbot in Nginx plugin mode, which automatically configures the SSL directives in the Nginx config
5. **Reload Nginx** after verifying the configuration syntax to apply all changes without downtime

